Introduction

Jiwon is a South Korean singer, dancer, rapper and actress, formerly under FNC Entertainment, FNC W and BlockBerryCreative. She was a member and the Lead Vocalist, Lead Dancer, Lead Rapper, Visual and Center of the girl group Cherry Bullet.

On January 21, 2019, she made her official debut as a member of the South Korean girl group Cherry Bullet with the single mini album "Let's Play Cherry Bullet" with "Q & A" serving as the title track.

In 2021, she appeared as a contestant on Mnet's survival show, “Girls Planet 999”. The show began airing on August 6 and ended on October 22. Unfortunately, Jiwon was eliminated in the eighth episode, with her final rank being K16.

On May 2023, she was confirmed as a constant of Mnet's newest survival show, "Queendom Puzzle". The show began airing on June 13, but Jiwon was eliminated in the semi-final, her final rank being 15th.
